Refs and ref resolutions are validated as part of CoreAlgorithmContext.Validate. Refs must have an existing FromSpec (the spec that declared the ref), must not self-reference, must not contain duplicate (from, to) pairs, and the directed ref graph must be acyclic (DFS-based cycle detection enumerating all back-edges). Refs whose ToSpec does not exist are NOT rejected here — they surface as TodoBrokenRef drift items so the user can fix the spec text or restore the missing spec. Ref resolutions must reference a spec pair connected by a declared ref edge (in either direction) and must not contain duplicate (reviewed, source) pairs. The acyclic check uses deterministic iteration order so cycle error messages are stable. See principles.specs_are_truth.